In a @medium pot{}, combine @water{3%cups} and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil,
then reduce heat to a low simmer. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice half the @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Core, deseed, and dice
@bell pepper{1}(deseeded and diced) into ½-inch pieces. Thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced),
separating whites from greens. Mince @chili pepper{1}(minced). Zest and quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, @ancho chili powder{1%teaspoon}, and
@garam masala{1%teaspoon}.

> For 4 servings, use 6 cups water, 2 teaspoons smoked paprika, 2 teaspoons ancho chili powder,
and 2 teaspoons garam masala.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add diced onion.
Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add @arborio rice{3/4%cup}; stir until translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add ½ cup stock; stir until
liquid has mostly absorbed. Repeat with remaining stock, adding ½ cup at a time and stirring
until liquid has absorbed.

When all the stock has been used, add @coconut milk{5.07%ounce}. Cook, stirring constantly,
until rice is al dente and mixture is creamy, ~{25-30%minutes}. (You'll start the fish
after 15 minutes.)

Meanwhile, pat @steelhead trout{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Season flesh sides with spice mix (it's OK if not all the spice sticks).

Once risotto has cooked ~{15%minutes}, heat a drizzle of oil in a second large,
preferably #nonstick pan{}, over medium heat. Add trout, skin sides down. Cook until skin is
crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}. (TIP: Lower heat if skin begins to brown too quickly.) Flip and cook
until opaque and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}.
Wipe out pan.

== Spicy Pepper Relish ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for trout over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper,
scallion whites, and a pinch of chili to taste; cook, stirring, until slightly softened,
~{6-8%minutes}.

Stir in @red pepper jam{1}, @sugar{1/4%teaspoon}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and season with a pinch of @salt{}.

== Finishing ==

Once risotto is done, turn off heat and stir in lime zest, @butter{1%tablespoon},
@salt{1/2%teaspoon}, and a squeeze of lime juice. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide risotto between #bowls{}. Top with trout. Spoon pepper relish over trout. Sprinkle with
scallion greens. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> For 4 servings, use 1½ cups butter and adjust seasoning accordingly.